The Cradle: the idea behind the cradle is that it consists of some I/O routines, an error-handling routine and a skeleton to the rest of the compiler build.

Chapter 2 Summary: Building a simple parser
  o No variables were allowed, only numeric factors
  o No limitations on number of digits!!
  
Feel free to try:

1+2 
1+2-9
8*45
2+31-2-0
-1
(4+5)/9

!!Another advenced feature!! 

our compiler knows how to recognize '( )' in math expression. 
feel free to try assignments like: x= x+3 -2 -(5-4) etc.

etc.
